headline.main: JAPANESE BREACH CHANGTEH DEFENSE; Chinese Battle in Streets to Hold Gateway to Changsha -- Reinforcements Near STILWELL FLIERS ACTIVE 14th Air Force Bombers Aid Assault on Foe's Positions Along Salween River

lead_paragraph: CHUNGKING, China, Nov. 30 (U.P.) -- The Japanese have broken into Changteh, key highway junction in northern Hunan Province, and savage street fighting is raging in the city, the Chinese High Command announced tonight.
abstract: French Indo-China: US planes sink Jap freighter, Gulf of Tonkin
